article.headline: Dartmouth 70, UC Davis 67
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Johnathan Ball and DeVon Mosley each scored 13 points and Alex Barnett added 12 points and seven rebounds to help Dartmouth hold off UC Davis 70-67 Monday night. Vince Oliver scored a game-high 19 points to lead UC Davis (4-4), which got 12 points and seven rebounds from Shane Hanson and 10 points from Mark Payne. Dartmouth (4-4) used a 10-0 run to build its largest lead of the night, 47-37, with 13:42 remaining, but had to hit its final six field goal attempts and four free throws in the last 18 seconds to squeeze out the victory. Mosley's two foul shots with 3.9 seconds remaining gave the Big Green a 3-point lead. The Aggies inbounded and rushed the ball up the left side, but a 3-point attempt by Payne bounced off the rim.
